<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06219033 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06219033 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  ADVERTISING; COMPANY; MANAGEMENT; CHANGE; APPOINTMENT; NAME  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  Saatchi andamp; Saatchi Advertising Worldwide, New York named Edward L. Wax aschairman and Richard Humphreys as president to consolidate the chain ofcommand in the Saatchi andamp; Saatchi empire.;    The agency, which is owned bySaatchi andamp; Saatchi PLC, London, also announced that the two men will be seniormembers in a new four-person office of the chief executive that will managethe agency.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Business  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  SAATCHI andamp; SAATCHI NAMES TOP EXECS  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     Wax, 54, had previously been chief executive of Saatchi andamp; SaatchiAdvertising North America, New York, one of the two divisions that make upSaatchi andamp; Saatchi Advertising Worldwide. The other, Saatchi andamp; SaatchiAdvertising International, London, had been the responsibility of Humphreys,45, the chief executive.;    Wax and Humphreys succeed the agency'sco-chairmen, O. Milton Gossett and Stuart Upson, who announced plans to stepdown two years ago.;    The appointments create a more centralized managementteam to oversee the two divisions of Saatchi andamp; Saatchi Worldwide, which in thepast have informally coordinated their activities.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  New York Times  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Stock Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910806  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Tuesday  </DAY><MONTH>  August  </MONTH><PG.COL>  5C  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  163  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Tuesday August 6, 199100219033,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>